~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
Out of the dark oblivion... Malaehi regains consciousness. Warily, she lets her elven ears pick up the sounds around her before she stirs. Locked in the dungeon room in the bowels of Felwithe, she has lost track of day and hour. Everything is eerily quiet and the stale scent of smoke permeates the air indicating the candles had been blown out about an hour ago. <br>
<br>
Slowly Mala raises herself from her crumpled position on the floor. Agony slams into the back of her skull and throbs at her temples. She gingerly moves her hand to the back over her head, feeling the dried blood matting her hair. The wound must be days old now. <br>
<br>
Her mind flashes back to the face of the guard assigned to her quarters, a masked Koada’dal Imperial guard of Erollisi Marr. How could one who serves the Goddess of Love cause this kind of agony, she wondered with fresh tears threatening to fall from her weary eyes. <br>
<br>
And there is when she had her moment of clarity... the followers and fanatics of the Gods are the ones missing the point, twisting things to suit their need for power and dominion. Nay, she could not hate her Goddess for the actions of Her blind followers. <br>
<br>
Malaehi slowly rose to her feet, steadying herself against the wall as a wave of nausea came over her. After emptying the meager contents of her stomach, ready to pass out again, she felt a cool draft of air as her chamber door silently opened behind her. <br>
<br>
Mala froze, then squared her shoulders and through her clenched teeth she said “<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>If you came to finish your job, then do so you pathetic coward daring to wear the uniform of our Goddess... Go on end my life before I slip myself onto your blade.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->”<br>
<br>
Malaehi heard the sharp gasp from the intruder behind her, as she turned her nose caught the familiar scent of roses. In the doorway, stood the High Elven Priestess Kae, her face displaying shock and horror as she looked upon Malaehi’s condition, robe ripped to shreds, dried blood staining her back and shoulders of her tattered gown, bloodshot defiant eyes overpowering her deathly pale face. The stench of the cell was overpowering so Kae grabbed Malaehi by the arm and led her into the dark corridor, bidding her to be silent.<br>
<br>
For what seemed like hours, Malaehi was led through corridor after corridor, twisting and turning, seemingly going deeper into the dungeon. Once they got to a dead end, Kae chanted some soft words and the two of them slipped on a cloak of invisibility and passed through the wall as if it were air. <br>
<br>
The cool fresh air brought the exhausted Enchantress back to her senses as she realized that Kae had led her outside. Turning to see the pool of water, Malaehi stumbled over, fell to her knees and drank like a madwoman. <br>
<br>
Kae watched all of this with her heart in her throat. Once her thirst was slaked, Malaehi slipped into the pool of water to bathe hissing in pain as the water stung her wounds on her back and head. <br>
<br>
Just then a cloaked figure approached Kae, then turned and whispered a few words in Mala’s direction. The enchantress felt her body levitate from the water then felt the electric tingle as her body was surrounded by the blue aura of a Cleric’s touch. Kae offered her hand and Malaehi walked across the air, approaching her and the cloaked Cleric. <br>
<br>
She heard the cleric cough discreetly, a male voice, when she realized her state of undress. Kae offered her a fresh robe which she quickly donned.<br>
<br>
“<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Will there be anything else, Mistress Kae?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->” the cleric asked. Kae handle him a heavy sack of coin and answered “<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Just your silence, Vicar</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->”. His head nodded under his heavy hood, then Kae chanted an invisibility spell and he vanished. Kae then chanted the words that would erase his memory in a reoccurring fashion. <br>
<br>
After a few more minutes, Kae turned to Malaehi. “<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>You must leave here and never return Malaehi d’Aeliu. You have broken your vow of chastity and attempted to take your own life.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->” Malaehi tried to interject, but Kae’s hand came up quickly to silence her. “<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>These are punishable by death, child.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->” <br>
<br>
“<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Does it matter naught that I am sorry...that I ... regret EVERYTHING I have done?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->” Mala pleaded. <br>
<br>
Kae pulled her close, looking into her eyes, searching... “<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Do you? Do you regret everything Malaehi, my child? The passion you felt? The love you made?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->” <br>
<br>
Malaehi pulled away as if stung, snorting “<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Bah, love... where is this love of mine? Mallo Artanos was right I perceive... he came took what he wanted from me. I was foolish to be lead by my feelings... I knew NOTHING of the man Nathomin... nothing of his deceitful past.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->” <br>
<br>
Malaehi inhaled deeply and stared off into the distance. “<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>So...? Now he has gone.  AND I do not feel at home in the House of Mallo and his Lions.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->” She turned to look at Kae defiantly “<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>He did not even TRY to come save me from this prison I have been in here?  And where are the Lions?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->”<br>
<br>
Kae turned away from the raw hurt that Malaehi was displaying, unable to form the words to make the situation change. “<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>It has come to pass, young one. And... you are stronger from this ordeal.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->”<br>
<br>
Malaehi chuckled bitterly “<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Strong, you say? I feel ... hollow.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->” She closed her eyes and inhaled the cool night air deeply, letting a cleansing breath flow freely. <br>
<br>
When she opened her eyes, their color cooled slightly. “<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>My heart belongs to me, and I will never waste this precious gift again.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->” She captured Kae’s gaze “<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Not for any man, not again.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->” <br>
<br>
Then, she quietly took her bags and silently disappeared into the night in search of her own path. Not of Lion's not of a man's.... but of her own.<br>
<br>
Kae suddenly felt very, very old as her heart weighed heavy in her chest, knowing that her daughter still had more ahead of her. With a whispered prayer of protection, Kae faded into the shadows of the Castle.<br>
<br>
The end. <p>Malaehi d'Aeliu - Phantasmist, in the service of Erollisi Marr<br>
